Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the penne. Peel and grate the @garlic{3%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a large #bowl{}, combine one third of the garlic, @panko breadcrumbs{10}, @salt{1/4} and @water{2} for the breadcrumbs, then add the @British beef mince{240%g}.

Season with @ground black pepper{} and mix together with your hands. Roll into even-sized balls, 5 per person.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Pop the meatballs onto a large #baking tray{}.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until browned on the outside and cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The meatballs are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, when the water is boiling, add the @penne pasta{180} and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @olive oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

== Sauce ==

While the pasta cooks, pop another large saucepan on medium-high heat with the @finely chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1/2%can}, @red wine jus paste{15%g} and @Italian style herbs{1}.

Stir in the @sugar{1} and @water{100} for the sauce and half of the remaining garlic. Simmer for ~{5-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, drain and tear the @mozzarella{1}. Pat dry with #kitchen paper{}.

Halve the @ciabatta{1} and spread over the remaining garlic. Drizzle with the @olive oil{1} for the garlic bread.

== Assemble and Bake ==

Once the meatballs and pasta are cooked, stir them into the sauce along with the @Parmigiano Reggiano{40%g} and half the mozzarella.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed. Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick, then transfer to an #ovenproof dish{}.

Top with the remaining mozzarella.

Pop the pasta bake on the top shelf of your oven and bake until golden, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, wash up the (now empty) baking tray. Pop the garlic bread onto it and set aside.

When 4 mins of baking time remain, bake the garlic bread on the middle shelf until golden, ~{3-4%minutes}.

== Salad and Serve ==

When everything's ready, pop the @baby leaf mix{50%g} into a bowl with a drizzle of @olive oil{} and toss together.

Share your ultimate meatballs and pasta al forno between your plates. Add the salad to your plates alongside and drizzle over the @balsamic glaze{12%ml}.

Serve with the garlic bread alongside. Enjoy!